main event: A UFO sighting report from Oahu, Hawaii, on 4 October 1964, includes analysis of photos taken at Kaiona Beach Park.
interesting points: The report mentions a single object sighted and evaluated through photographs taken on 9 October 1964., Photos A and B were taken within one minute of each other and show possible UFO phenomena., The photos were processed locally, and there were no defects found in the film., The report concludes that the flashes in the photos were a result of film processing errors., A previous analysis by the Director of Intelligence concurred with the evaluation presented.
sighted object: possible UFO phenomena captured in Kodacolor prints
witness description: The observers were military personnel from a Naval Station in Hawaii.
